name: Liliana's Mastery
oracle_text:
Zombies you control get +1/+1.
When Liliana's Mastery enters the battlefield, create two 2/2 black Zombie creature tokens.
flavor_text: "There are so many of them. It seems they've just been waiting for someone to serve."

name: Lord of the Accursed
oracle_text:
Other Zombies you control get +1/+1.
{1}{B}, {T}: All Zombies gain menace until end of turn.
flavor_text: The Curse of Wandering leaves only hatred.

name: Murmuring Mystic
oracle_text: Whenever you cast an instant or sorcery spell, create a 1/1 blue Bird Illusion creature token with flying.
flavor_text: Rumors float through the city like crows, alighting on citizens seemingly at random.

name: Plea for Power
oracle_text: Will of the council — Starting with you, each player votes for time or knowledge. If time gets more votes, take an extra turn after this one. If knowledge gets more votes or the vote is tied, draw three cards.

name: Jeering Homunculus
oracle_text: When Jeering Homunculus enters the battlefield, you may goad target creature. (Until your next turn, that creature attacks each combat if able and attacks a player other than you if able.)
flavor_text: Mklthd had always hated crowds . . . and they had always hated him.

name: Illusory Ambusher
oracle_text:
Flash (You may cast this spell any time you could cast an instant.)
Whenever Illusory Ambusher is dealt damage, draw that many cards.
flavor_text:
"Violence is the food it craves. Feed it if you dare."
—Doriel, mentor of Mistral Isle

name: Impulse
oracle_text: Look at the top four cards of your library. Put one of them into your hand and the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.
flavor_text: "You call it luck. I call it preparation."

name: Fleshbag Marauder
oracle_text: When Fleshbag Marauder enters the battlefield, each player sacrifices a creature.
flavor_text: Grixis is a world where the only things found in abundance are death and decay. Corpses, whole or in part, are the standard currency among necromancers and demons.

name: Fog Bank
oracle_text:
Defender, flying
Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt to and dealt by Fog Bank.
flavor_text:
"The union of sea and sky makes a perfect cover."
—Talrand, sky summoner

name: Counterspell
oracle_text: Counter target spell.

name: Diluvian Primordial
oracle_text:
Flying
When Diluvian Primordial enters the battlefield, for each opponent, you may cast up to one target instant or sorcery card from that player's graveyard without paying its mana cost. If a spell cast this way would be put into a graveyard, exile it instead.

name: Fact or Fiction
oracle_text: Reveal the top five cards of your library. An opponent separates those cards into two piles. Put one pile into your hand and the other into your graveyard.
flavor_text: "Try to pretend like you understand what's important."

name: Brineborn Cutthroat
oracle_text:
Flash (You may cast this spell any time you could cast an instant.)
Whenever you cast a spell during an opponent's turn, put a +1/+1 counter on Brineborn Cutthroat.
flavor_text: "I always attack from where their spyglasses can't see."

name: Angler Turtle
oracle_text:
Hexproof
Creatures your opponents control attack each combat if able.
flavor_text: It is ancient, immense, and irresistible.

name: Angler Drake
oracle_text:
Flying
When Angler Drake enters the battlefield, you may return target creature to its owner's hand.
flavor_text: From the time they are hatchlings, river drakes are taught to pull the largest prey from the Luxa.

name: Valorous Stance
oracle_text:
Choose one —
• Target creature gains indestructible until end of turn. (Damage and effects that say "destroy" don't destroy it.)
• Destroy target creature with toughness 4 or greater.
flavor_text:
"Every choice alters the path of fate."
—Sarkhan Vol

name: Vow of Duty
oracle_text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature gets +2/+2, has vigilance, and can't attack you or planeswalkers you control.
flavor_text:
"I prefer loyalty to be a matter of respect, not of magic. But one does what one must."
—Kaalia of the Vast

name: Strength of Arms
oracle_text: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn. If you control an Equipment, create a 1/1 white Human Soldier creature token.
flavor_text:
"We fight not for Avacyn, but for her ideals; not for the church, but for its people."
—Thalia, Guardian of Thraben

name: Swords to Plowshares
oracle_text: Exile target creature. Its controller gains life equal to its power.
flavor_text: "The arc of my blade has carved a path of light for the peace that will follow."

name: Kor Outfitter
oracle_text: When Kor Outfitter enters the battlefield, you may attach target Equipment you control to target creature you control.
flavor_text: "We take only what we need to survive. Believe me, you will need this."

name: Path to Exile
oracle_text: Exile target creature. Its controller may search their library for a basic land card, put that card onto the battlefield tapped, then shuffle.

name: Pilgrim of the Ages
oracle_text:
When Pilgrim of the Ages enters the battlefield, you may search your library for a basic Plains card, reveal it, put it into your hand, then shuffle.
{6}: Return Pilgrim of the Ages from your graveyard to your hand.

name: Serra Angel
oracle_text: Flying, vigilance
flavor_text: The angel remembers her past lives like dreams. Her song held up meadows. Her blade drove back darkness. Her wings carried her across the ages.

name: Forbidding Spirit
oracle_text: When Forbidding Spirit enters the battlefield, until your next turn, creatures can't attack you or planeswalkers you control unless their controller pays {2} for each of those creatures.
flavor_text: "You will respect the dead."

name: Heavenly Blademaster
oracle_text:
Flying, double strike
When Heavenly Blademaster enters the battlefield, you may attach any number of Auras and Equipment you control to it.
Other creatures you control get +1/+1 for each Aura and Equipment attached to Heavenly Blademaster.

name: Kitesail Apprentice
oracle_text: As long as Kitesail Apprentice is equipped, it gets +1/+1 and has flying.
flavor_text: Carving lines through the sky, kite sailors map trails for the pilgrims below to follow.

name: Kor Duelist
oracle_text: As long as Kor Duelist is equipped, it has double strike. (It deals both first-strike and regular combat damage.)
flavor_text: "Swords cannot reach far enough. Chains cannot strike hard enough. An eternal dilemma, but a simple one."

name: Banisher Priest
oracle_text: When Banisher Priest enters the battlefield, exile target creature an opponent controls until Banisher Priest leaves the battlefield. (That creature returns under its owner's control.)
flavor_text: "Oathbreaker, I cast you out!"

name: Captain of the Watch
oracle_text:
Vigilance (Attacking doesn't cause this creature to tap.)
Other Soldier creatures you control get +1/+1 and have vigilance.
When Captain of the Watch enters the battlefield, create three 1/1 white Soldier creature tokens.

name: Danitha Capashen, Paragon
oracle_text:
First strike, vigilance, lifelink
Aura and Equipment spells you cast cost {1} less to cast.
flavor_text: "I will protect the less fortunate. I will love bravely. I will face despair and fight on. As a Capashen, I can do no less."

name: Ancestral Blade
oracle_text:
When Ancestral Blade enters the battlefield, create a 1/1 white Soldier creature token, then attach Ancestral Blade to it.
Equipped creature gets +1/+1.
Equip {1} ({1}: Attach to target creature you control. Equip only as a sorcery.)

name: Cyclone Summoner
oracle_text: When Cyclone Summoner enters the battlefield, if you cast it from your hand, return all permanents to their owners' hands except for Giants, Wizards, and lands.
flavor_text: Frost giants study for centuries in isolation, honing their ability to harness elemental mayhem.

name: Valkyrie Harbinger
oracle_text:
Flying, lifelink
At the beginning of each end step, if you gained 4 or more life this turn, create a 4/4 white Angel creature token with flying and vigilance.
flavor_text: Where she flies, the Light of Starnheim shines.
